  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD053116",
      "title": "Angiotensinogen and C3 compete for renin-induced complement activation",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Demonstration of renin cleavage of C3. Angiotensinogen and C3 compete for renin-induced complement activation.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Renin from Abcam (ab135012), 1 \u00b5L (1 mg/mL) was reduced and alkylated. Digestion was performed by adding Lysyl Endopeptidase (Wako), Mass Spectrometry Grade 10AU, Product number: 129-02541) to the samples and incubated overnight at 37 \u00b0C. The digestion was stopped by 10 \u00b5L 10% trifluoroacetic acid. The samples were placed in a Speed Vac until dry. The samples were resolved in 10 \u00b5L 2% acetonitrile (ACN) containing 0.1% trifluoroacetic acid (TFA. The sample was analyzed on an Exploris 480 mass spectrometer (Thermo Fischer Scientific) coupled with a Vanquish Neo UHPLC system (Thermo Fischer Scientific). Two-column setup was used on the HPLC system and peptides were loaded into an Acclaim PepMap 100 C18 precolumn (75 \u03bcm x 2 cm, Thermo Scientific, Waltham, MA) and then separated on an EASY spray column (75 \u03bcm x 25 cm, C18, 2 \u03bcm, 100 \u00c5, ES902) with the flow rate of 300 nL/min. The column temperature was set 45 \u00b0C. Solvent A (0.1% FA in water) and solvent B (0.1% FA in 80% ACN) were used to create a 30 min nonlinear gradient from 5 to 25% of solvent B for 25 min and increased to 28% for 3 min and the increased to 30% for 2 min to elute the peptides. The samples were analyzed with a data-dependent acquisition (DDA) in positive mode. The full MS1 resolution were set to 120,000 at m/z 200 and the normalized AGC target was set to 300% with the maximum injection time of 45 ms. The full mass range was set 375-1500 m/z. Precursors were isolated with the isolation window of 1.3 m/z and fragmented by HCD with the normalized collision energy of 30. MS2 was detected in the Orbitrap with the resolution of 30,000. The normalized AGC target and the maximum injection time were set to 100% and auto, respectively. The intensity threshold for precursor selection was set to 8.0e3 and 30s dynamic exclusion was applied.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Raw DDA data were analyzed using Proteome Discoverer\u2122 2.5 Software (Thermo Fisher Scientific). Peptide identification employed SEQUEST HT and Mascot against the UniProtKB human (UP000005640), Bovine (UP000009136) and a contaminants fasta file from Max Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried. The search parameters included static modification (cysteine carbamidomethylation) and dynamic modifications (N-terminal acetylation, oxidation of methionine). Precursor tolerance was set to 10 ppm, and fragment tolerance was set to 0.02 ppm. Up to 2 missed cleavages were allowed, and Percolator was employed for peptide validation at a maximum q-value of 0.05. Extracted peptides were used for identification. Only high confident peptides were considered for protein identification.",
